sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K180012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Rock - Primary plasmid (part 2) [tac pR, mCherry and LasI generator]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: See relevant basic biobrick parts (K180000, B0034, K180008, B0015)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Part of the iGEM2009 Team:Southampton rock-paper-scissors 'rock' primary plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Regulated expression of LasI (C0178) and mCherry (K180008) by tac pR (K180000), controlled by presence of lac/IPTG or trp in the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Wilson, Stephanie Chambers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K180000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Hybrid promoter (trp & lac regulated -- tac pR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The Ptac promoter is a functional hybrid promoter, derived from the trp and lac promoters, that are regulated by trp and lac [1]. The Ptac sequence has been extracted by PCR from the commercially available plasmid pMAL-pIII from New England Biolabs (N8101S), with the addition of the biobrick prefix and suffix sequences.
[1] Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, Vol. 80, pp. 21-25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Sequence includes lacIq and Shine-Dalgarno sequence from pMAL-pIII prior to the Ptac promoter to ensure correct functionality of the promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Wilson, Stephanie Chambers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K180008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mCherry fluorescent protein - Rights owned by Clontech. Sequence is commercially available from Clontech. Sequence obtained through PCR amplification, with BioBrick prefix and suffix added through in-house designed primers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: PstI site within the mCherry sequence - has to be assembled using BioBrick assembly in such an order that any successive digestions will not require PstI, otherwise the mCherry sequence will be cut as well as the site of interest.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Wilson, Stephanie Chambers
